EXECUTIVE SUMMARY AND RECOMMENDATIONS
This analysis examined long-term performance, risk, and inter-relationships of the NIFTY50, NIFTY100, and NIFTY500 indices using 10+ years of daily aggregated data.
KEY FINDINGS
•	NIFTY500 exhibits the strongest long-term growth (~11.7% annualised vs ~8.4% for NIFTY50) but with consistently higher volatility
•	Very high correlation (0.94–0.98) between indices, particularly NIFTY100–NIFTY500
•	Volatility spikes (e.g. March 2020) disproportionately affect NIFTY500
•	Box plots reveal wider dispersion and more outliers in NIFTY500 returns
RECOMMENDATIONS
1.	Diversify beyond NIFTY50: allocate 20–40% to NIFTY100 or NIFTY500 to capture higher expected returns
2.	Use NIFTY100 as cost-effective proxy: high correlation with NIFTY500 but lower volatility
3.	Implement volatility-based risk controls: reduce exposure during sustained high-volatility periods
4.	Strategic value: These insights enable more informed asset allocation, improved risk-adjusted returns, and differentiated client advisory in the Indian equity market.
